# Home Parity Fixes Specification

## Purpose

Match the approved Home visual reference while preserving search, favorites, and navigation behavior exactly.

## Requirements

### Requirement: Runtime sync baseline

The app launch flow MUST not race with stale node/expo processes during visual validation.

#### Scenario: Validation starts from a clean runtime
- GIVEN a prior Expo or Node process is running
- WHEN visual validation begins
- THEN the stale process is stopped before a new launch is used for evidence

### Requirement: Header, search, and chips parity

The Home shell MUST present a single header composition with search affordance, avatar affordance, and category chips with balanced spacing across narrow and wide viewports.

#### Scenario: No duplicate chrome is visible
- GIVEN the Home screen is open
- WHEN the shell renders
- THEN there is only one header/chip composition

### Requirement: Card hierarchy and overlay parity

Content cards MUST preserve the image-first hierarchy, readable metadata placement, and visible overlay actions without changing favorite behavior.

#### Scenario: Media metadata remains readable
- GIVEN a visible content card
- WHEN it renders
- THEN the title and subtitle hierarchy remain clear and the overlay icons stay within the media bounds

### Requirement: Bottom tab balance parity

The bottom tab bar MUST use spacing and sizing that visually balance the icon and label stack on both phone-width and wider screens.

#### Scenario: Tabs remain balanced
- GIVEN the app is open on Home or Favorites
- WHEN the bottom bar renders
- THEN icon and label spacing stay centered and consistent

### Requirement: Verification and rollback safety

The change MUST include cmux-browser verification checkpoints and clearly documented rollback notes.

#### Scenario: Validation evidence is captured
- GIVEN the UI has been updated
- WHEN browser validation runs
- THEN phone and wider viewport evidence is captured

## Out of Scope

- No data fetching changes
- No repository/domain changes
- No search or favorite logic changes
- No navigation route changes
